  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "MV",
    "text": "In-- in-- in my mother's flowerbed or in the cellar. We keep things in the cellar, too-- maybe in the cellar. [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] This is a picture of me when I was about 17 or 18. And that is my mother and father and my sister when we were already in the ghetto. They look very sad. They didn't know where their four sons and two son-in-laws were. These pictures are in my niece's book. The book is called And, uh, it was-- um, I don't know exactly when it was, uh, published. It was published by the University of Illinois Press. [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] This picture was taken of me when I was 17 years old, I think. I'm not sure. It was taken by a boyfriend. And it's also in my Niece's book. [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] This book, the of was written by my niece, Judith Magyar Issacson, published by the University of Illinois Press. The name refers to an event which happened after we were-- we were chased to go on a trip. And the Germans already know-- knew [? the war ?] getting to be [? over. ?] And we went from camp to camp, walking and being very sick, most of us, and tired. And they said, 'you better go and stay in the group and walk or you will to be shot to death. There will be no seed of Sarah. Everybody will be shot.' That's the name of the-- that's why the name of the book is My niece has three children, seven grandchildren, and I have three great grandchildren, so the lives on. [PAUSES FOR 17 SECONDS] This is a prayer book for the United States Army for Jews in the army. And after we were liberated, I don't know how soon, a month or two or a few weeks after, a Rabbi came with some officers and gathered us together and give each of this book. To tell you the truth, we were not too happy about it because we rather would have gotten some bread and all kinds of food and juice or whatever because we were still very hungry. [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] This is my son Andrew, who is, in my unbiased opinion, the best son in the world, and his wife [? Judith. ?] The both just are wonderful people. They have a little daughter Rachel.",
