  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "MV",
    "text": "About five years ago-- four, five years ago. I really don't know. I should know. This picture is showing my son, who's holding his two children's arms. My grandson, Stewart, who just graduated in June. And that picture was taken on graduation day, day June 19, 1995. And my granddaughter Lori, who is 15. It was taken in Highland Park, Illinois. [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] This is a picture of my husband, me, and little Rachel. It was taken here in the front of our condo in February, 1995. He passed of 18 months ago. We would have had our 48th wedding anniversary September 7. He loved me. He loved his son. He adored his three grandchildren. And that little baby just stole his heart. We all will miss him very much. [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS]",
